  "text": "Remark 3. This example shows that the MDS code can be avoided when q is sufficient large. This is because, thanks to the repetition code, the entire matrix A, and hence the product (1), can be recovered by combining the information available at the non-straggling servers when we store uncoded rows from matrix A. As compared to the policy in [CITATION_1] , a higher storage redundancy r 2 = Kµ = 3 is obtained for the repetition code. As a result, the multicasting gain Kµ = 3 can be reaped in the shuffle phase, while the maximum gain for [CITATION_2] is limited to 2. Hence, the proposed scheme achieves a lower communication load.",
